content.text:
- **Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))  
  - “SR-4835, a highly selective dual inhibitor of **CDK12** and **CDK13**, which disables **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)** cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))  
  - “promoting synergy with DNA-damaging chemotherapy and **PARP inhibitors**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))  

- **CDK12 Inhibition Reverses De Novo and Acquired PARP Inhibitor Resistance in BRCA Wild-Type and Mutated Models of Triple-Negative Breast Cancer** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27880910/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27880910/))  
  - “**dinaciclib**, an inhibitor of cyclin-dependent kinases (CDKs) 1, 2, 5, and 9, additionally has potent activity against **CDK12**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27880910/))  
  - “support the broad use of combined **CDK12** and **PARP inhibition** in **TNBC**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27880910/))  

- **CDK inhibition results in pharmacologic BRCAness increasing sensitivity to olaparib in BRCA1-WT and olaparib resistant in Triple Negative Breast Cancer** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38574883/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38574883/))  
  - “the broad range **dinaciclib** and the **CDK12-specific SR-4835**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38574883/))  
  - “both CDKis showed synergism with **olaparib**, as well as with **cisplatin** and **gemcitabine**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38574883/))  

- **Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  
  - “a potent **PROTAC degrader PP-C8** based on the noncovalent dual inhibitors of **CDK12/13**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  
  - “**PP-C8** demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with **PARP inhibitor** in **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  

- **Discovery of a novel dual-target inhibitor of CDK12 and PARP1 that induces synthetic lethality for treatment of triple-negative breast cancer** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37478560/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37478560/))  
  - “a series of small molecule inhibitors targeting both **CDK12** and **PARP1** were designed and synthesized.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37478560/))  
  - “The new dual-target inhibitor (**12e**) showed potent inhibitory activity against **CDK12 (IC_{50} = 285 nM)** and **PARP1 (IC_{50} = 34 nM)**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37478560/))  

- **A phase 1 study with dose expansion of the CDK inhibitor dinaciclib (SCH 727965) in combination with epirubicin in patients with metastatic triple negative breast cancer** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25947565/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25947565/))  
  - “**dinaciclib (SCH 727965)** in combination with **epirubicin**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25947565/))  
  - “Trial registration:  ClinicalTrials.gov **NCT01624441**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25947565/))
